UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1814
1 AN ACT relating to the supervision of pharmacy technicians.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 315.020 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) An[No] owner of a pharmacy who is not a pharmacist shall [fail to ]place a
5 pharmacist in charge of his or her pharmacy and[or] shall not permit any person to
6 compound or dispense prescription drugs, medicines, or pharmaceuticals in his or
7 her place of business except in the presence and under the immediate supervision of
8 a pharmacist.
9 (2) A[No] manufacturer of pharmaceuticals who is not a pharmacist shall [fail to ]place
10 a pharmacist in charge of his or her place of business and[or] shall not permit any
11 person to compound prescription drugs, medicines, or pharmaceuticals in his or her
12 place of business, except as provided by the board through the promulgation of
13 administrative regulations pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A.
14 (3) Except as provided in subsection (4) of this section, a[no] person shall not engage
15 in the practice of pharmacy unless licensed to practice under the provisions of KRS
16 Chapter 315.
17 (4) The provisions of subsection (3) of this section shall not apply to:
18 (a) Pharmacist interns performing professional practice activities under the
19 immediate supervision of a licensed pharmacist. The nature and scope of the
20 activities referred to in this paragraph shall be determined by the board
21 through administrative regulation promulgated pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A;
22 (b) Pharmacist interns and pharmacy technicians performing specifically
23 identified pharmacy practice activities while under the supervision of a
24 pharmacist. The nature and scope of the activities referred to in this paragraph
25 shall be determined by the board through administrative regulation
26 promulgated pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A;
27 (c) Other licensed health care professionals practicing within the statutory scope
