UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1814
1 of their professional practices; or
2 (d) Volunteer health practitioners providing services under KRS 39A.350 to
3 39A.366.
4 (5) (a) As used in this subsection:
5 1. "Order entry" means the process by which pharmacy personnel validate
6 prescription data and enter that data into a pharmacy's dispensing or
7 medication management system. Prescription data includes but is not
8 limited to patient demographics, prescriber demographics, drug name,
9 strength, dosage form, quantity, the directions for use, refill
10 authorization, or any clarifications of the same; and
11 2. "Order entry verification" means the process by which a pharmacist
12 verifies prescription data entered in a pharmacy's dispensing or
13 medication management system after order entry has been completed.
14 (b) Nothing in this chapter shall prohibit a pharmacist licensed in Kentucky, or a
15 pharmacy technician registered in Kentucky or a pharmacy intern certified in
16 Kentucky who is working under the supervision of the pharmacist, from
17 accessing the electronic database of the pharmacy, from inside or outside of
18 the pharmacy, to perform order entry, order entry verification, or drug
19 regimen review as defined in KRS 315.010, if:
20 1. The pharmacy has established controls to protect the confidentiality and
21 integrity of protected health information;
22 2. No part of the pharmacy's database is duplicated, downloaded, or
23 removed from the electronic database; and
24 3. The pharmacy is located in Kentucky and is permitted by the board.
25 (c) Supervision required by paragraph (b) of this subsection may include
26 electronic supervision.
27 (d) This subsection shall only apply to:
Page 2 of 3
