UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1814
1 1. Pharmacies that are not open to the public and do not dispense to walk-
2 in patients in a retail setting; or
3 2. Hospitals licensed under KRS Chapter 216B.
4 (e) Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to authorize final product
5 verification and dispensing of a prescription from a location outside of or
6 other than a pharmacy.
7 (f) Nothing in this subsection permits pharmacists, pharmacy technicians, or
8 pharmacy interns to receive hard copy prescriptions outside of the premises of
9 a permitted pharmacy.
10 (g) The board shall not require the immediate supervision by a pharmacist of a
11 pharmacist technician engaging in the stocking, retrieving, or returning of
12 product to or from the pharmacy inventory, including the stocking and
13 loading of an automated filling or dispensing system with the use of barcode
14 technology, under this subsection.
15 (6) Effective April 1, 2009, an owner of a pharmacy shall not employ a person to assist
16 in the practice of pharmacy unless the person is registered as a pharmacy technician
17 by the board or exempt under KRS 315.135.
